  "text": "Factors (e.g., Mx1) T cells [CITATION_1] , and is elevated in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) of patients with HIV-associated dementia compared with neurocognitively normal HIVinfected patients [CITATION_2] . Mamik and Ghorpade [12 & ] extended these studies and found that CXCL8 increased formation of 2 long terminal repeat (2-LTR) circles, a marker of nuclear import of viral DNA or enhanced infectivity, in macrophages and primary microglia and that enhanced replication was dependent on nuclear factor of kappa light polypeptide gene enhancer in B-cells (NF-kB).",
